observe.desc:
[
{A feline Abnormality that has unusually large eyes. Though nearly entirely furless, the end of its tail is rich with red fur.}
]

[
{An unusually small lion was left alone in a Forest, shunned by everyone for being a coward. What approached him was a rusted Tin Woodsman, a Scarecrow with an empty head, and a girl in silver shoes. The lion, wishing for courage, joined the daring little girl and her friends in hopes of fulfilling his own wish.}
]

[
{And so the lion and his friends found their way to the great Wizard and each told her their wish. The lion fully believed the Wizard when she said he would gain unmatched courage, and drank the clear liquid she handed him. The cowardly lion of the Forest was a coward no more, and returned to the Forest leaving his friends behind. He believed he would no longer be scared by anything.}
]

      [
      {However, a different fear creeped back into the lion now that he was alone once more. Without his fiends, is there a reason for him to exist? What am I now, left all alone again?

And so the small lion hid away in the forest, surrouned by the fear of loneliness. After spending what seemed like an eternity cowering, what appeared in front of him once again was the three friends he had journeyed together with. Without hesitation, the lion vowed to follow his friends on the endless road, and courage started to well up inside him like magic. There's nothing to fear when everyone is together. The only fear, is that of being alone.}
      ]

[
{And so, the fur of the lion with his regained courage was stained red by the blood of those trying to separate them. The lion existed to be with his friends, to grant the wishes of his friends. The more people he fell, the more courage he gained, and his plentiful fur was painted more red by the day.}
]
